  "texts": [
    "Let ∇ ad, h be a connection and bundle metric on adM, and let g B be a metric on B.",
    "The tension field of h is the section τ (h) ∈ Γ Sym 2 (adM) * defined by(14) τ (h) = -2h(∇ +, * θ•, •),where ∇ ad = ∇ + + θ is the (unique) decomposition of ∇ ad into a connection ∇ + preserving h, and a h-self adjoint End(adM)-valued one-form θ (cf.",
    "Lemma 2.18).In Definition 2.16, we use the Levi-Civita connection to extend the covariant derivative ∇ + to act on End(adM)-valued tensors.",
    "Moreover, ∇ +, * denotes the formal adjoint of ∇ + with respect to the L 2 -inner product on End(adM)-valued tensors induced by h and g B.",
    "On End(adM)-valued one-forms, it is given by(15) ∇ +, * θ = - dim B i=1 (∇ + Xi θ) Xi.The Ricci curvature of (M, g) can then be expressed in terms of the Ricci curvature of (B, g B), the Ricci curvature of the fibres (with the induced metric), and the tensors A and T; see [Bes87] or [BL23a, Theorem 2.2].Proposition 2.17."
